e first time in records of Arab-Persian merchants and seamen during the years 1993-2093. In the name of the city of Singkur or Singkara, but in the books of natural history and politics of the Kingdom of Siam Mr. Khalas Saraswati called the name of Songkhla "Muang Singkhon" and therefore assumed that the word Songkhla was derailed from the name "Singhala" (read Sing-Ha-La) or Singkhon. The reason that Songkhla is called Singha Laeng means Muang Sing. By getting this name from Persian merchants, India sailed for trading Saw the island of ko, the cat island when looking far Will see two lion statues crouched at the entrance to Songkhla city Indians therefore called this city Singha La, while Thailand called the city of Sting when Malay came to contact with the city of Sting, also called Singha La but pronounced distorted as a Western accent, namely Singora Thai. Called by the Malay and Western sounds. Distortion is Songkhla. Another reason claimed that Songkhla derives from "Singkhon" meaning mountain, claiming that the city of Songkhla is located at the foot of the red mountain. Subsequently, the royal title was given to Songkhla that "Wichian Khiri", which has a meaning corresponding to the topography Back ////VERSION//// Version: 1.0.1 Supported by : Academic Service Center,Prince of Songkla University ////Rating///// ฺVery Bad Bad Fair Good Excellent Please Select Rating //// Gallery //// Location More images Website ///More-Choose-District/// Muang District Hatyai District Other District ////QueasTion/// You have already answered the questionnaire. ////CHECKIN-SEARCH/// Search for places ////BACK//// Please click BACK again to exit
